{
  "texts": [
    "As long as the diagnosis follows the same clinical guidelines, it receives an accuracy score of 4 or 5.",
    "• If the final diagnosis is completely wrong and has no clinical impact, it receives an accuracy score of 0 or 1.",
    "However, if the essential diagnosis is completely wrong and has a clinical impact, it is always scored as 0.",
    "• If the diagnosis is in the correct spectrum, but there is variation in subjective assessment, it often receives an accuracy score of 3.",
    "For example, hypertrophic or bowenoid actinic keratosis vs. squamous cell carcinoma in situ."
  ]
}